ISLAMABAD (Reuters) - Leaders of Pakistan’s coalition government on Tuesday set about seeking a replacement for President Pervez Musharraf and tackling pressing economic and security problems.

Pakistan's President Pervez Musharraf leaves the presidential house after his resignation in Islamabad August 18, 2008. Musharraf announced his resignation on Monday in the face of an impending impeachment motion by the ruling coalition government. REUTERS/Mian Khursheed
